## Step 3 completion (2026-04-29)

`03_train_stage1.py` written and run.  LightGBM with native NaN
handling on a 51-feature matrix (probe channel harmonised across
755252/767022 (514) and the spot subjects (561) into `cprobe_*`).

**LOSO mean AUC = 1.000 — this is *not* a real result.**
The GBT is trivially memorising the heuristic rules, since the rule
columns (`c405_peak_inside`, `solidity`, `volume_um3`,
`c405_core_minus_shell_p90`, `boundary_touching`) are the top-5
features by mean gain.  Most folds early-stop at 1–10 iterations.
Real validation requires Step 5 with human labels.

**Operationally useful, however.**  On the *uncertain* rows (those
that match no rule) the score spreads across 0.3–0.9 (60–100 % of
uncertain cells fall in [0.3, 0.7] depending on subject; none below
0.3).  Plenty of material for the GUI's uncertain-band sampling.

