### GUI design
- ipywidgets + matplotlib + ipyevents (keyboard).
- 6-panel display per ROI (top: 405 MIP / 488 MIP / overlay; bottom:
  three 405 z-slices through the centroid), mask outline overlaid
  in red, side panel with the 14 highest-signal features.
- Buttons + keyboard shortcuts: `g` good, `b` bad, `u` unsure, `s`
  skip, `z` undo.
- Append-only `outputs/roi_qc_actions.jsonl`; `_undone_` records
  carry the original record so `label_progress()` excludes them.
- `launch(sid, n_rois=80, score_band=(0.3, 0.7), reviewer="...")`.
- Resume-safe: prior labels for the same `(sid, hcr_id)` are
  excluded from the sample pool on next launch.

### Sample previews
`outputs/previews/preview_*.png` (6 ROIs from 788406, score 0.40–0.51)
— borderline-but-real cells with imperfect mask outlines, exactly
the cases this GUI is meant to disambiguate.

### Recommended labelling protocol
- ~50–100 ROIs / subject from the [0.3, 0.7] uncertain band.
- 6 subjects × 80 ROIs ≈ 480 labels.  Target ~5 s / ROI -> 40 min
  per labelling pass.
- Reviewer name goes in every record so multiple reviewers can be
  combined (e.g. inter-rater agreement) later.

